"T hadlong since considered, that the way to please the best judges, is not to translate a poet literally, and Virgil least of any other; for, his peculiar beauty lying in his choice of words, I am excluded from 1t by the narrow compass of our heroic verse, unless T would make use of monosyllables only, and those clogged with eonsonants, which are the dead weight of our mother-tongue. It is possible, I con- fess, though it rarely happens, that a verse of mono- syllables may sound harmoniously ; and some ex- amples of it T have seen. My first line of the ZEneis is not harshâ€”"